==Direct objects== The word {{term-fa|را|râ}} marks definite direct objects in Persian. That is,
Colloquially, {{Persian/text|را}} is pronounced ‹ro› after a vowel or ‹o› after a consonant.
In written Persian, {{Persian/text|من را|man râ}} may contract to {{Persian/text|مارا|mârâ}}, but colloquially pronounced ‹mano›. Similarly, written {{Persian/text|تو را|to râ}} can contract to {{Persian/text|تورا|torâ}} but colloquially pronounced ‹toro›.
