{{ingredient}}

Curry Leaf is used in most [[Cookbook:Cuisine of India|Indian]] delicacies, it adds flavor and spicy pleasant smell to the dish. Typically, is [[Cookbook:Frying|fried]] during ''tadka'' or ''bhagaar'' - the process of frying spices before adding [[Cookbook:Vegetable|vegetables]] for making [[Cookbook:Curry|curry]].

Can be found in most Indian grocery stores.

